ved. We conclude\nthat accurate MASC observations of the microphysical, orientation, and fall\nspeed characteristics of snow particles require shielding by a double wind\nfence and restriction of analysis to events where winds are light (<5 m/s).\nHydrometeors do not generally fall in still air, so adjustments to these\nproperties' distributions within natural turbulence remain to be determined.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Jul 2020 17:16:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-22"}
