nmore accurate estimate of the FIR-$z$ uncertainty with reduced chi-squared of\norder $\\mathcal{O}(\\chi^2_{\\nu})=1$, compared to alternative far-infrared\nphotometric redshift techniques (with\n$\\mathcal{O}(\\chi^2_{\\nu})\\approx10-10^{3}$).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Jul 2020 18:00:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-09"}
